 On Aug 11, Jens Axel Søgaard wrote:
 > The link at <http://www.drscheme.org/docs.html>
 > has a text saying "All PLT Documentation".
 > However, the page <http://download.plt-scheme.org/doc/>
 > does not include a list of all doc.txt files from
 > the various collections. 
 > 
 > A first time user might be misled to believe that
 > the collections doesn't have documentation.
 
 I always viewed doc.txt files as extensive+searchable readme files,
 unlike stuff in collects/docs which I took as the bunch of manuals you
 get with the software.  Adding the doc.txt files to the web page is
 probably not feasible without a major restructuring of the whole
 thing, so I guess that the only solution to this semi-problem is a
 better link name, but I can't think of anything better that fits
 within three words.
 
