Subject: Re: all/6983: Documentation missing on homepage
Date: Thu, 12 Aug 2004 07:13:05 -0400

 On Aug 11, Robby Findler wrote:
 > Putting the doc.txt files onto the web wouldn't be a bad idea, imo
 > (planet does/will do this, I think?).
 > 
 > But if it's not feasible, perhaps just putting a warning about it on
 > the documentation web page is enough?
 
 The download/docs hierarchy is not too flexible...  Currently there
 is:
 
   <version>/bundles/<doc>.plt
   <version>/html/<doc>/...
   <version>/pdf/<doc>.pdf
 
 symbolic links to the last released version
 
   <doc> -> <last-version>/html/<doc>/
 
 one such link is to an old version
 
   mrspidey -> 103p1/html/mrspidey/
 
 icons are for some reason taken from 205 (they're not in newer
 builds):
 
   icons -> 205/html/icons/
 
 and the nightly builds are
 
   pre-release -> ../scheme/docs
 
 Adding doc.txt files into this will make it even more messy.  Adding a
 sentence that there are doc.txt files in packages seems like the best
 solution for now.  One of the things I want to get to at some point is
 go over the iplt/web tree and make it actually build *everything* in
 the web hierarchies, creating a self-containing result that will
 replace the existing trees, rather than copying stuff on top of what's
 there.  This would be a good time to add the doc.txt files.  Older
 versions would be included in iplt/web as .tgz files.
 
 BTW, I prefer if these are kept to the minimum of only the .plt files
 that are needed for older versions -- there is a lot of traffic on the
 older htmls, because they tend to be better indexed (they're much
 older), so the effectiveness of googling is also limited by them, and
 there are probably lots of cases of people mislead or confused by
 them.  I don't think that it's a big deal if older drscheme versions
 will not be able to browse these things on-line if it is still
 possible to install them locally.  (There are ways of dealing with
 search engines, but it will be difficult to do this right.)
 
 (It's probably best if replies to this will go to plt-internal.)
 
 
 On Aug 12, Jens Axel Søgaard wrote:
 > Hm - a search box on <http://download.plt-scheme.org/doc/> would
 > also be nice.
 
 There is a search box on the pre-release pages, but it's not too great
 because of the above.
 
 I suppose that it would be possible to run a help-desk server, but the
 current hierarchy will make it pretty difficult to manage.
 
 -- 
