Subject: Re: all/6983: Documentation missing on homepage
Date: Thu, 12 Aug 2004 09:38:31 -0400

 On Aug 12, Robby Findler wrote:
 > At Thu, 12 Aug 2004 07:13:05 -0400, Eli Barzilay wrote:
 > > (There are ways of dealing with search engines, but it will be
 > > difficult to do this right.)
 > 
 > Were you thinking of putting robots.txt files in older versions? 
 
 You can't -- it must be at the server's top level, so the file will
 have to be rebuilt for every version, forbidding indexing on the
 previous one, which is a fragile solution.  Google has extensions to
 the format that allows you to put wildcards, but that's not the
 standard (IIRC).  A reasonable solution would be to have the old
 versions in some directory that can be completely excluded, but I
 think that it's a bad idea to keep the content...
 
 (Another solution which is even worse is a script that will crawl over
 the tree and change each file so it forbids indexing in its meta
 tags.)
 
 -- 
